      <p>As presented in <xref ref-type="table" rid="molecules-10-00481-t002">Table 2</xref>, we obtained cinnamic acids <bold>3a-g</bold> in yields which ranged from 53 to 81%, depending on the reaction conditions and structure of the aldehydes <bold>2</bold>. The cinnamic acid <bold>3d</bold> was obtained in the lowest yield due to the presence of the methoxy (&#x2013;OCH<sub>3</sub>) group which has an electron donating effect. The cinnamic acids with electron withdrawing groups were obtained in good yields.</p>
